The paper discusses the privacy risks associated with machine learning models, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the interpretability of machine learning models, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attacks performed in the paper involve analyzing the training data, which is a task related to data mining (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.DB.
